Drives phase 2 of the cage lifecycle: starts the API proxy for billed modes, execs the caged process via `bwrap`, and tears the proxy down once the cage exits. Its single entry point, `run_until_exit(r: &Resolved, prep: &Prep) -> Result<i32, CageError>`, is what `lifecycle::mod` calls after `prepare::Prep` has built the run dir; return value is the cage's process exit code (defaults to `1` if the child was killed by a signal).

The proxy is only started when `mode_is_billed(&r.mode)` is true (checked via `crate::cli::mode_is_billed`) — self-test and non-billed interactive runs skip it entirely. `start_proxy` binds a Unix socket at `prep.rundir.join(API_SOCK_NAME)`, removing any stale file first, and spawns an accept loop thread (`proxy::serve`) stopped later via an `AtomicBool` flag plus `join()`. Auth is passthrough: `ProxyConfig.api_key` is always `None` — the caged claude's own OAuth header goes straight through, so no key is ever injected server-side. Correspondingly, `cage_env` never sets `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`; doing so would trigger claude's interactive "use detected API key?" prompt inside the sandbox. `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` is set to `CAGE_BASE_URL` (from `crate::runtime`) only in billed mode, pointing claude at the in-cage relay instead of the real API.

`exec_cage` builds a `BwrapConfig` (from `crate::bwrap`) and shells out to `bwrap` directly via `Command`, skipping `argv[0]` since `build_bwrap_args` includes the program name as first element — this must stay in sync with whatever `build_bwrap_args` puts there. `Mode::Interactive` sets `new_session: false` (keeps the TTY session for interactivity); other modes set `new_session: true`.

Environment construction is layered: `base_env` sets PATH (cage tools + optional cargo bin + `/usr/bin:/bin`), fixed identity (`HOME=/tmp`, `USER=cage`), locale, inherited `TERM` (via `host_term`, falling back to `xterm-256color` for TUI palette correctness), and `CARGO_NET_OFFLINE=true`. `cage_env` layers on `CTX_TASK_BRIEF` for `Mode::Task` and the billed-mode base URL. `--clearenv` is implied — comments state this is the *complete* environment, nothing else leaks through from bwrap's flags (defined elsewhere in `crate::bwrap`).

`toolchain_home`/`toolchain_dirs` resolve `CARGO_HOME`/`RUSTUP_HOME` from env vars or `~/.cargo`/`~/.rustup` defaults, filtering to existing directories only — silently omits toolchain binds/env if absent, no error. `detect_secret_masks` checks only `.env` and `.git/config` relative to `target_root`, existence-based, feeding into `BwrapConfig.secret_masks` (mask mechanics live in `crate::bwrap`, not here).

`tool_binds` mounts `ctx-verify`/`ctx-context`/`ctx-scan` always, and — when `prep.claude` is `Some` — binds the claude binary twice (once at `CAGE_BIN/claude` on PATH, once at `CAGE_LOCAL_CLAUDE`, the installer-check path claude probes under its home) plus the RO credential at `CAGE_CLAUDE_CRED`. `claude_rw_binds` is the only writable bind for claude tooling: the synthesized `~/.claude.json` at `CAGE_CLAUDE_CONFIG`, because claude rewrites that file at runtime.

`self_test_stub_cmd` embeds a shell script probe (used by `Mode::SelfTestStub`) checking: workspace writable, secrets present-but-unreadable-as-empty (not literally unmounted — a mask that makes files vanish broke git previously, hence the specific "readable as empty" requirement), git functional, and no network egress (attempts a socat connection to `1.1.1.1:80` and fails the probe if it succeeds). It writes only under `target/` per ADR-027, and is cwd-relative per ADR-046 — moving invocation directory breaks it silently.

`claude_cmd` starts an in-cage socat relay forwarding `127.0.0.1:8080` to the bind-mounted proxy socket at `/run/ctx/{API_SOCK_NAME}` before exec'ing claude with `--dangerously-skip-permissions`; the comment asserts the cage itself is the sandbox that flag assumes exists. `headless: bool` selects `-p` (non-interactive, takes `$CTX_TASK_BRIEF`) vs. interactive claude invocation. Both branches append the system prompt from `CAGE_RULES_PATH` (`prep.rules_file`, written by `prepare::Prep`).